==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stop-gap
<hw>Stop"-gap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which closes
or fills up an opening or gap; hence, a temporary expedient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Moral prejudices are the <qex>stop-gaps</qex> of virtue.</q>
<rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stoping</ent>⟦br⟧
